         <abstract>
            <p>Recently B. R. Santos conjectured that 12 is the largest integer $n$ with the following property: \begin{equation*}\tag{*} \begin{cases} \text{ If } m \in \lbrack 1, n \rbrack \text{ and } n \text{ are relatively prime, then \\ n + m \text{ is a prime number }.\end{cases}\end{equation*}. Using deep numerical estimates of Rosser and Schoenfeld for the number $\pi(x)$ of primes less than $x$, it is proved that the conjecture of Santos is true. The same result holds, if in addition it is assumed in $(\ast)$ that $m$ is a prime.</p>
          </abstract>
